Installation:

    git clone https://github.com/NgoPCuong/dotfiles.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

Contain Plugins:
    Fugitive
    Nerdtree
    SimpylFold
    Syntastic
	indentPython
    ctrlp
    vim-airline


Shortcuts Key:
  Space  enable folding class/method
  Ctrl-j move to the split below
  Ctrl-k move to the split above
  Ctrl-l move to the split to the right
  Ctrl-h move to the split to the left
  Ctrl-n opens nerdtree



YouCompleteMe Installation for Mac:

1. install macvim
    homebrew install macvim
2. point vim to your macvim using ~/.bash_profile
    alias vim="/usr/local/Cellar/macvim/8.0-120/MacVim.app/Contents/MacOS/Vim"
    alias vi="vim"
3. Then follow the instructions on:
    https://github.com/Valloric/YouCompleteMe

